      "date": "2013-07-08 06:58:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is going to be another huge one. Running the sed script generated\n\n307 files changed, 3538 insertions(+), 3410 deletions(-)\n\nIt is even larger than the libcfs_mem patch. So I want to ask what to do with it? Shall I submit without converting any source files and do the conversion incrementally later on?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5e8ef8014189fcd13a72b155d44b7e7f8b45b7fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-08 22:26:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think it makes sense to split this into smaller chunks.  I would guess that the atomic_* operations make up most of the changes in the code, and the rest of the changes would have very little effect on the main code.\n\nIt should hopefully be possible to leave the old cfs_atomic_*->atomic_* macros in place to minimize disruption, convert the cfs_atomic_* macros in the current code in 2 or 3 patches, then wait a few weeks and do a final patch to remove the old cfs_atomic_* macros and any remaining callers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
